    "body": "This is no bug, and the warning tells you what you did wrong.\r\n> expected variable, string, textgroup, or conditional\r\n\r\nAs long as you don't want the brackets (`[]`) in the output—than you would need to escape them (like `\\[\\]`)—, all brackets need to be accompanied by parenthesis (`()`).\r\n\r\nTherefore, your string:\r\n```toml\r\nformat = \"[[](bold bg:#93bcfc) [$symbol $branch ]($style) ]\"\r\n```\r\nwould have to be, either:\r\n```toml\r\nformat = \"[[](bold bg:#93bcfc) [$symbol $branch ]($style) ](fg:yellow)\"\r\n```\r\nor, it would also work as:\r\n```toml\r\nformat = \"[[](bold bg:#93bcfc) [$symbol $branch ]($style) ]\"\r\n```\r\n\r\n",
