    "body": "I took the liberty, to update your configuration in a way you would probably like to use. I changed the format section to be better readable and added a conditional for the `[git_branch]` and `[git_status]` module, as either of those could be rendered alone (e.g. if `HEAD` is detached).\r\n\r\n```toml\r\nformat = \"\"\"\\\r\n\t[ ╭](bold fg:purple)$username[─](bold fg:purple)\\\r\n\t[](bold fg:#9db4fb)$directory[─](bold fg:#9db4fb)\\\r\n\t(↓ Git information are only shown, if either a git_branch or a git_status is available ↓)\\\r\n\t(\\\r\n\t\t[](bold fg:#93bcfc)\\\r\n\t\t$git_branch\\\r\n\t\t$git_status\\\r\n\t\t[](bold fg:#8cc2fd)[─](bold fg:#8cc2fd)\\\r\n\t)\\\r\n\t[](bold fg:cyan)$cmd_duration[](bold fg:cyan)\\\r\n\t$line_break\\\r\n\t$character\\\r\n\"\"\"\r\n\r\n# …\r\n\r\n[git_branch]\r\nformat = \"[$symbol $branch]($style)\"\r\nstyle = \"bold fg:black bg:#93bcfc\"\r\nsymbol = \"\"\r\n\r\n[git_status]\r\nahead = \"⇡${count}\"\r\nbehind = \"⇣${count}\"\r\ndeleted = \"x\"\r\ndiverged = \"⇕⇡${ahead_count}⇣${behind_count}\"\r\nformat = \"([ \\\\[$all_status$ahead_behind\\\\]]($style))\"\r\nstyle = \"bg:#8cc2fd fg:black\"\r\n\r\n# …\r\n```",
